title: Last French D-Day fighter dies aged 100
description: The last surviving French D-Day fighter, Leon Gautier, has died aged 100.

title: Students 'absolutely traumatised' as deaths of two classmates on Greek island investigated
description: Greek police are investigating the deaths of two Irish teenagers who were celebrating the end of their school exams on the island of Ios.

title: Police arrest mother of seven-year-old girl whose body was found decaying in wardrobe
description: Police in the US have arrested the mother of a seven-year-old girl whose body was found decaying in the wardrobe of a vacant apartment.

title: Deaths of mother and seven-year-old son after falling off ferry 'not an accident'
description: An investigation has revealed the deaths of a Polish mother and her seven-year-old son after they fell off a ferry last week was not an accident.

title: 'Lightning hunter' animations show spectacular storms across Earth
description: Spectacular animations showing lightning storms across the Earth have been put together with data from a new satellite project that will make it easier for forecasters to predict severe storms.

title: Police chief says rioters 'are there to kill us' in French town where mayor's home attacked
description: The police chief in a French town reeling from an attack on its mayor's home has told Sky News his officers are involved in "a war" against rioters "who are there to kill us".

title: Barbie movie banned in Vietnam
description: Warner Bros' long-awaited Barbie movie has been banned in Vietnam.

title: Irish police find body at major tourist attraction in missing person case
description: Police in Ireland searching for a man who went missing on one of the country's major tourist attractions after an alleged assault have found a body.

title: K-pop band Blackpink make history as Hyde Park headliners
description: Blackpink have made history as the first Korean group to headline a major music festival in the United Kingdom.

title: Outrage in Philippines after tourism ad uses footage from other countries
description: A tourism agency has apologised after a video advertising the Philippines as a holiday destination showed footage from other countries.

title: Four injured after building explosion in Tokyo
description: Four people have been injured following an explosion at a building in Tokyo, Japanese media reported.

title: Titan sub victims spent final moments listening to music in dark, report reveals
description: The people on board the doomed Titan submersible spent their final moments listening to music and watching bioluminescent creatures in darkness, according to a new report.

title: Firefighter dies after another night of violence in France
description: A firefighter has died in France after responding to a blaze in an underground car park, the interior minister has said.

title: Missing teenager found alive more than eight years after disappearance
description: A missing Texas teenager has been found alive after disappearing more than eight years ago.

title: At least seven Palestinians killed as Israeli airstrikes target West Bank city of Jenin
description: The Israeli military has carried out airstrikes on the northern West Bank town of Jenin overnight, and large numbers of soldiers were reported in the area as part of a new and major operation to target "extensive counter-terror activity".

title: Violence and looting subsides in Nanterre and Paris - but it is an uneasy calm
description: In their line of riot vans, the police sat ready on the edge of Nanterre.

title: Grandmother of teen shot by police appeals for calm as 3,000 arrested during unrest in France
description: The grandmother of the teenager whose death sparked riots across France has appealed for calm, as the total number of arrests has risen above 3,000.

title: Award-winning Ukrainian writer Victoria Amelina dies after missile strike on pizza restaurant
description: Award-winning Ukrainian writer Victoria Amelina has died from injuries sustained after a Russian missile hit a pizza restaurant in Kramatorsk on Tuesday.
